data.name: Coconut Cream Jello Shots
data.quickTastyDescription: Deliciously creamy coconut jello shots that are perfect for parties!
detailedCookingInstructions: In a small saucepan, combine 1 cup of coconut milk and 1 cup of water. Heat gently until warm but not boiling.
Remove from heat and sprinkle the unflavored gelatin over the warm mixture. Stir until completely dissolved.
Add sugar and stir until dissolved. If using rum, mix it in at this stage.
Pour the mixture into small cups or shot glasses, filling them about 2/3 full.
Refrigerate for at least 4 hours or until set.
Before serving, top each jello shot with whipped cream and a sprinkle of shredded coconut.
